Adeyinka Adedipe The Edo State Governor, Mr. Godwin Obaseki, has mourned the death of the Rector of Auchi Polytechnic, Dr Momodu Jimah, who died at 60. He died on Friday night around 7pm. The Public Relations Officer of the school, Mr. Mustapha Oshiobugie, confirmed the occurrence to Sunday PUNCH. Oshiobugie said, “I can confirm that he is no more and his remains have been committed to mother earth on Saturday by 10 am according to Muslim rites.” The governor, in a statement, said Dr Jimah was an astute administrator who contributed to the growth of Auchi Polytechnic, ensuring stability and development of the institution. Obaseki said,“It was with a heavy heart that I received news of the passing of the Rector of Auchi Polytechnic, Dr Momodu Sanusi Jimah. I condole with the management, staff and students of the institution over his death.’’. Copyright PUNCH.
